column5: Hey all.....    Cap'n Wayne   Terry at the helm   $1.27!!!!!!!!   Wayne, Mike and Terry   The docking arrangements leave a lot to be desired, here is one of the victims, Gerritt   Joe, cooking some of those killer vegs!!!   Peter and the lovely Joey   Ok, here is my arguement, this is a species of esox, of which the pickeral is also a member, so why didnt I win the tourney????     You want extreme fishing? Ted was actually using his filet knife to scrape his rides windshield!!   Catch of the day!   Worshipping at the feet of Walleye Dan, why you ask? Because I get results!!!!!   See?   Fish in the boat.   Lovely golden colour...at this point I figured if I caught a sheephead, I'd have a Quinte grand slam!!  I had a wonderful time, fished with some good people, hung out with some good people and had a lot of laughs. Thanks to all who were there.
those fish look real good   who photoshopped them in for you guys...LOL
LOL ! That the best pic you could find Cap'n Dan ?  ..and yah had to be there to get your $1.27 worth !
OMG $1.27 i dont think ive ever laughed so hard LOL Great Post and it was great meeting you hope to see you next year!! BMM
Hahahaha, those are awesome pictures.  They sure show how much fun we had.  Great report and it was a pleasure gabbing with you again, as always. Joey
Dang, did it AGAIN, twice in one night.  Gotta get my own puter  Joey
Nice report Dano. Missed this one, but I'll be back.
$1.27 must have been metric measurement. Great to meet you Dan and a pleasure sharing a cabin with you. BTW, beauty pickeral and a nice walleye too! -Brian

LOL...great report...very funny!!  The size of the screen on that sonar/gps is bigger than my living room TV....haha.  Fishing was tough, but you guys managed to boat some  It was great seeing you...hope to meet up again!
~~~And the great post keep on comen, makes sitten at my desk a lot easier, thanks for sharing
Lotsa hilarious stuff there Dan, good to hear you enjoyed the trip so much !!
